URL: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/8164&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/8164&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;   This PR enhances the epoch checking logic for endTransaction call in TransactionCoordinator. Previously it relaxes the checking by allowing a producer epoch bump, which is error-prone since there is no reason to see a producer epoch bump from client.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   Since this is purely a server side bug which requires no client side change, we haven&apos;t added any integration test to verify this behavior yet.&lt;/p&gt;

